WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.215 --> 00:00:02.928
<b>Previously on Stargate Atlantis...</b>

2
00:00:03.721 --> 00:00:05.057
You have some wraith DNA.

3
00:00:05.057 --> 00:00:08.021
- You can actually see what's happening?
- I'm on a ship.

4
00:00:08.021 --> 00:00:09.440
Receiving an IDC.

5
00:00:09.482 --> 00:00:11.367
- Who is it?
- Stargate Command.

6
00:00:11.403 --> 00:00:14.157
All we have to do is hold down
until the Daedalus get's here

7
00:00:14.157 --> 00:00:16.897
then we could use the ZPM to power the city shield.

8
00:00:17.122 --> 00:00:21.077
Multiple signals Sir. We couldn't see
them until they were right on top of us.

9
00:00:22.924 --> 00:00:25.387
The colonel Marshall Sumner
was a very good friend of mine

10
00:00:25.387 --> 00:00:28.142
You admit to firing the shot that killed him.

11
00:00:28.183 --> 00:00:30.731
The Wraith... they are in Atlantis.

12
00:00:30.897 --> 00:00:32.692
They're sending in another wave.

13
00:00:32.692 --> 00:00:35.113
Fly the puddle jumper in stealth
mode right down their throats.

14
00:00:35.113 --> 00:00:36.950
You are volunteering for a suicide mission?

15
00:00:36.950 --> 00:00:39.413
- You can't.
- I have to. and you know it.

16
00:00:46.802 --> 00:00:49.849
Teyla I'm hearing gun fire.
what's your status.

17
00:00:50.058 --> 00:00:50.773
<i>Teyla?</i>

18
00:00:56.695 --> 00:00:59.785
Mecanism armed and ready. I'm going in.

19
00:01:01.622 --> 00:01:03.102
And now the conclusion.

20
00:01:04.376 --> 00:01:05.670
Defense!

21
00:01:59.229 --> 00:02:01.233
Major Sheppard. decloak your jumper immediately.

22
00:02:01.233 --> 00:02:04.071
What? Who the hell is this?

23
00:02:04.113 --> 00:02:07.453
Authentication. Alpha Charlie 1. Decloak now!

24
00:02:12.170 --> 00:02:17.012
Detonation in 5. 4. 3. 2...

25
00:02:32.124 --> 00:02:33.829
Target has been neutralised.

26
00:02:36.632 --> 00:02:37.676
He did it.

27
00:02:39.221 --> 00:02:41.892
Yeah he did.

28
00:02:44.272 --> 00:02:46.025
Dr Weir I'm picking up another ship.

29
00:02:46.025 --> 00:02:49.740
- Another hive ship?
- Negative. I'm reading an IFF.

30
00:02:49.991 --> 00:02:51.995
<i>Atlantis? This is Sheppard.</i>

31
00:02:54.040 --> 00:02:55.042
John?

32
00:02:55.042 --> 00:02:56.879
<i>What other Sheppards do you know?</i>

33
00:02:56.879 --> 00:02:58.131
Oh thank God!

34
00:02:58.173 --> 00:03:00.677
No. that can't be. We saw the hive ship go up.

35
00:03:00.677 --> 00:03:03.683
<i>I assure you Dr McKay that</i>
<i>Major Sheppard is alive and well.</i>

36
00:03:03.683 --> 00:03:04.602
Who is this?

37
00:03:04.602 --> 00:03:10.237
Colonel Steven Caldwell. Commander of the Daedalus.
We are ready to assist you.

38
00:03:11.323 --> 00:03:13.326
Oh thank you!

39
00:03:13.744 --> 00:03:15.854
We are very glad to hear it. Colonel.

40
00:03:17.751 --> 00:03:21.007
And I assume we have you to
thank for saving Major Sheppard.

41
00:03:21.049 --> 00:03:24.013
We were monitoring your transmissions
as soon as we came out of hyperspace.

42
00:03:24.013 --> 00:03:26.059
We couldn't beam him in until he decloaked his jumper.

43
00:03:26.059 --> 00:03:27.764
Didn't take much convincing.

44
00:03:28.145 --> 00:03:28.995
Dr McKay?

45
00:03:29.899 --> 00:03:30.776
Present! Yes!

46
00:03:30.776 --> 00:03:33.155
<i>I trust you know what to do with this?</i>

47
00:03:36.160 --> 00:03:37.371
Your ZPM sir.

48
00:03:41.629 --> 00:03:43.006
How did they do that?

49
00:03:43.006 --> 00:03:47.598
The Daedalus is loaded with Asgard technology.
Beaming technology is the first part of it.

50
00:03:47.682 --> 00:03:52.400
- They got things like...
- Rodney? What say we get the shields back up.

51
00:03:55.071 --> 00:03:56.115
What say we.

52
00:03:58.119 --> 00:04:00.163
We still have Wraith all over the city

53
00:04:00.163 --> 00:04:03.128
After we deal with those other hive ships.
we'll assist you as soon as we can.

54
00:04:03.128 --> 00:04:04.158
Caldwell out.

55
00:04:04.171 --> 00:04:07.344
Sir. we have incoming enemy fighters bearing 320.

56
00:04:08.930 --> 00:04:12.145
All forward rail guns. stand by. Launch all fighters.

57
00:05:46.822 --> 00:05:50.702
<i>Colonel Caldwell? This is Novak in engineering.</i>

58
00:05:50.743 --> 00:05:51.703
<i>What is it?</i>

59
00:05:51.744 --> 00:05:55.165
Hermiod wanted to remind you that our
shields strength will be severely diminished

60
00:05:55.165 --> 00:05:58.220
without the Zero Point Module
tied into our power systems.

61
00:05:58.628 --> 00:06:01.053
I'm well aware of that Doctor. Caldwell out.

62
00:06:02.341 --> 00:06:05.531
Major. do you recommend any
specific target on the hive ship?

63
00:06:05.846 --> 00:06:06.972
One of the fighter bays. Sir.

64
00:06:06.972 --> 00:06:09.183
That would increase the chance
of secondary explosions.

65
00:06:09.183 --> 00:06:10.601
That's what I was thinking. Sir.

66
00:06:10.601 --> 00:06:14.356
I agree. Waeps. arm two mark 8 tacticals.
Our target is the hive ships main fighter bay.

67
00:06:14.356 --> 00:06:16.693
Warheads armed. Target is locked Sir.

68
00:06:16.735 --> 00:06:17.405
Fire!

69
00:06:25.120 --> 00:06:26.580
We need to get in closer.

70
00:06:26.580 --> 00:06:29.375
Helm. alter heading to intercept. Go to max thrust.

71
00:06:29.417 --> 00:06:30.460
Max thrust.

72
00:06:30.501 --> 00:06:31.586
We'll just have to get closer.

73
00:06:31.586 --> 00:06:36.092
The Asgard gave you hyperdrives and shields.
How come. no offensive weapons?

74
00:06:36.134 --> 00:06:39.137
Providing other races with anything that
could be potentially used against them?

75
00:06:39.137 --> 00:06:40.797
I thought they were allies?

76
00:06:41.140 --> 00:06:44.375
Without their beaming technology.
you wouldn't be here. Major.

77
00:06:44.644 --> 00:06:45.979
Arm two more mark 8's.

78
00:06:45.979 --> 00:06:47.954
You're wasting ordinance. Colonel.

79
00:06:48.399 --> 00:06:51.634
Those missiles are being intercepted
miles from the hive ship.

80
00:06:56.493 --> 00:06:59.497
I've routed the shield's sub routine.
When I give the word. all you have to do is punch it...

81
00:06:59.497 --> 00:07:00.932
I know what to do. go!

82
00:07:05.337 --> 00:07:08.257
Whoa.whoa.whoa. what is this?
This is my security escort?

83
00:07:08.257 --> 00:07:10.343
Well we are spread a little bit thin right now.

84
00:07:10.343 --> 00:07:12.054
OK. but you need to know that if we come under fire.

85
00:07:12.054 --> 00:07:13.972
you're gonna have to put your
lives on the line to protect me.

86
00:07:13.972 --> 00:07:14.732
Rodney!

87
00:07:14.766 --> 00:07:17.394
OK.I mean the ZPM.
Protect the ZPM at all costs.

88
00:07:17.435 --> 00:07:19.188
And me! Am I wrong?

89
00:07:25.362 --> 00:07:26.948
- Dr Weir?
- Yes?

90
00:07:27.073 --> 00:07:29.200
I've lost contact with some of our people.

91
00:07:29.200 --> 00:07:30.369
Who?

92
00:07:30.411 --> 00:07:35.458
We can get a hold of the teams
led by Captain Radnor. Teyla or Lt Ford.

93
00:07:37.252 --> 00:07:38.462
Well keep trying.

94
00:07:50.060 --> 00:07:53.273
Now we're 0 for 2. How many things have you got?

95
00:07:53.314 --> 00:07:54.816
Only one needs to get through.

96
00:07:54.816 --> 00:07:58.654
Is there any way we can deliver a warhead
the same way you plucked me out of the Jumper?

97
00:07:58.654 --> 00:08:00.072
The Asgard have already considered that Major.

98
00:08:00.072 --> 00:08:03.285
There are failsafes built into the systems to prevent
their use as a weapons delivery system.

99
00:08:03.285 --> 00:08:08.040
You've got one of these Asgard onboard?
Can he override the failsafe?

100
00:08:08.082 --> 00:08:09.209
Why would he do that?

101
00:08:09.209 --> 00:08:11.949
Well. his butt's on the line. just as much as ours.

102
00:08:14.466 --> 00:08:17.136
Novak. I need you and Hermiod to figure out
how to get sight to sight transport

103
00:08:17.136 --> 00:08:19.263
locks on a set of coordinates inside the hive ship.

104
00:08:19.263 --> 00:08:24.228
No. no. Sir.
Hermiod isn't going to like that.

105
00:08:24.270 --> 00:08:26.335
<i>Get it done Doctor. that's an order.</i>

106
00:08:37.119 --> 00:08:38.779
That's where we have to go.

107
00:08:50.803 --> 00:08:51.971
What was that? I didn't get all that.

108
00:08:51.971 --> 00:08:55.746
What do I do? Look. I'm gonna get to
the rolling things. Maybe I can uh...

109
00:09:39.114 --> 00:09:39.906
Clear.

110
00:09:41.366 --> 00:09:43.453
No. no. You stay here.

111
00:09:50.545 --> 00:09:55.217
So! This is how it's gonna be?
Just me?

112
00:09:57.304 --> 00:09:59.514
OK. that's fine!

113
00:09:59.556 --> 00:10:02.560
You want some of this?

114
00:10:06.190 --> 00:10:08.818
This is McKay! I'm in trouble down here!

115
00:10:13.991 --> 00:10:15.659
Dr McKay? Are you alright?

116
00:10:15.659 --> 00:10:17.370
Teyla. we thought you were...

117
00:10:17.370 --> 00:10:21.209
My radio was broken and I was separated from my group.
I've been trying to make my way back.

118
00:10:21.209 --> 00:10:23.628
Oh thank God! You have no idea.
I thought I was gonna...

119
00:10:23.628 --> 00:10:24.963
I thought you were very brave.

120
00:10:24.963 --> 00:10:26.048
Really?

121
00:10:27.341 --> 00:10:29.886
- I have a ZPM.
- Yes.

122
00:10:29.969 --> 00:10:31.262
We need to get the shields up.

123
00:10:31.262 --> 00:10:33.641
- Lead the way.
- Yeah sure. After you.

124
00:10:39.189 --> 00:10:43.111
I've set the timer for 5 seconds.
Is that enough time for you?

125
00:10:43.152 --> 00:10:45.614
Five seconds should be more than ample.

126
00:10:47.867 --> 00:10:52.206
OK look. I know you don't approve of using
techology this way. but you have to understand...

127
00:10:52.206 --> 00:10:53.791
I am ready.

128
00:10:56.628 --> 00:11:00.174
Colonel. Hermiod is ready and
standing by for warhead transport.

129
00:11:00.174 --> 00:11:04.138
but I can tell you. he is not happy about this.

130
00:11:04.138 --> 00:11:08.101
I take that under advisement.
Are we within transport range?

131
00:11:08.101 --> 00:11:08.935
Yes Sir!

132
00:11:10.395 --> 00:11:12.145
Transport warhead when ready.

133
00:11:12.565 --> 00:11:17.404
Ready! 5... The weapon is away.

134
00:11:29.127 --> 00:11:32.092
We have a kill.
The last hive ship has been neutralised.

135
00:11:36.011 --> 00:11:38.389
Novak. I need you to prep
another warhead for transport.

136
00:11:38.389 --> 00:11:39.765
We need to take out those cruisers.

137
00:11:39.765 --> 00:11:40.850
Sir wait!

138
00:11:42.853 --> 00:11:45.940
Colonel. cruisers have broken off
and entered hyperspace.

139
00:11:45.982 --> 00:11:49.110
Seeing what we just did to
their remaining hive ships. I don't blame them.

140
00:11:49.110 --> 00:11:51.363
There are still a lot of Darts out there.

141
00:11:51.363 --> 00:11:52.531
Alright. let's clean this up.

142
00:11:52.531 --> 00:11:54.618
Sir. the Wraith fighters are regrouping.

143
00:11:54.618 --> 00:11:57.497
Everyone get into position.
Stand by for defensive fire.

144
00:11:57.497 --> 00:11:59.207
We're not the target.

145
00:11:59.457 --> 00:12:03.253
Major Sheppard is right. Sir.
The formation is headed toward Atlantis.

146
00:12:03.962 --> 00:12:05.847
Elizabeth. you've got a problem.

147
00:12:07.091 --> 00:12:08.384
Yeah. we see that Major.

148
00:12:08.384 --> 00:12:11.305
<i>We're moving to intercept.</i>
<i>but I don't think we can get there in time.</i>

149
00:12:11.305 --> 00:12:13.058
Not a chance. They're coming in too fast.

150
00:12:13.058 --> 00:12:15.852
Oh my God! Their approach is ballistic.

151
00:12:15.894 --> 00:12:17.146
And what exactly does that mean?

152
00:12:17.146 --> 00:12:20.859
Their impact velocities will be in excess
of 10.000 kilometres an hour.

153
00:12:21.068 --> 00:12:23.529
No part of the city can withstand that.

154
00:12:23.529 --> 00:12:25.323
You'd better get the damn shield up!

155
00:12:25.323 --> 00:12:26.991
How much time do we have?

156
00:12:27.867 --> 00:12:29.036
45 seconds.

157
00:12:30.412 --> 00:12:33.583
Rodney we need the shield up
in 40 seconds or we're dead!

158
00:12:33.625 --> 00:12:34.543
Are you kidding me?

159
00:12:34.543 --> 00:12:35.210
No!

160
00:12:35.252 --> 00:12:38.506
<i>I think we're nearing the point</i>
<i>in which I completely snap.</i>

161
00:12:38.548 --> 00:12:39.674
Rodney!

162
00:12:41.844 --> 00:12:44.681
That should do it! Fire it up!

163
00:12:49.562 --> 00:12:51.021
That didn't do it.

164
00:12:51.063 --> 00:12:52.440
- What?
- It is not working.

165
00:12:52.440 --> 00:12:54.550
- I know what she said!
- 20 seconds.

166
00:12:54.568 --> 00:12:57.947
Okay. Snap! That's it!
Are you all happy now?

167
00:12:58.030 --> 00:13:03.288
- Rodney!
- OK. OK. OK! Try it now!

168
00:13:22.352 --> 00:13:25.064
Atlantis? This is Sheppard. Come in.

169
00:13:27.234 --> 00:13:28.277
Atlantis?

170
00:13:37.955 --> 00:13:40.000
<i>This is Sheppard. What is your status?</i>

171
00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:42.212
The explosions must have disrupted the radio signal.

172
00:13:42.212 --> 00:13:46.133
We're still here. That's our status.

173
00:13:48.219 --> 00:13:49.846
Don't scare me like that.

174
00:13:49.888 --> 00:13:52.557
<i>Sorry. What about the Wraith fleet?</i>

175
00:13:52.641 --> 00:13:55.336
The remaining cruisers have withdrawn from battle.

176
00:13:55.895 --> 00:13:59.525
Thank you Colonel. Thank all of you.

177
00:13:59.566 --> 00:14:02.737
Glad to be of help. We're gonna stay in
Geosynchronous orbit for the time being.

178
00:14:02.737 --> 00:14:04.364
Can we be of any further assistance?

179
00:14:04.364 --> 00:14:06.492
We could use some help with the Wraith in the city.

180
00:14:06.492 --> 00:14:09.547
We're sending some people to help with that.
Daedalus out.

181
00:14:11.164 --> 00:14:14.669
Major Sheppard. I'm sure you're
anxious to get back to Atlantis.

182
00:14:14.710 --> 00:14:16.964
Yes Sir! Thank you.

183
00:14:22.846 --> 00:14:25.850
<i>Rodney? You can take the rest of the day off.</i>

184
00:14:28.269 --> 00:14:33.109
I'm going to curl up in bed with
the largest sandwich I can find.

185
00:14:34.527 --> 00:14:39.382
Shall I just explain to the rest of the Wraith left
on the base. that you're unavailable to fight?

186
00:14:41.077 --> 00:14:42.161
Right.

187
00:14:59.767 --> 00:15:04.315
Secure Stargate Operations. Hello. I'm home!

188
00:15:18.373 --> 00:15:19.792
Yes you are.

189
00:15:22.712 --> 00:15:23.964
I truly thought...

190
00:15:23.964 --> 00:15:27.154
Yeah. yeah. I thought the same
thing about you. a minute ago.

191
00:15:27.552 --> 00:15:28.970
We gotta stop that.

192
00:15:29.429 --> 00:15:30.556
I'd like that.

193
00:15:33.893 --> 00:15:35.729
So uh. where are we?

194
00:15:36.563 --> 00:15:38.775
Well most of our sensors are still down.

195
00:15:38.775 --> 00:15:41.861
but we do know that there are at least
a handful of Wraith still in the city.

196
00:15:41.861 --> 00:15:43.155
Still got some work to do.

197
00:15:43.155 --> 00:15:46.705
Before you do anything.
Colonel Everett insists on speaking with you.

198
00:15:47.619 --> 00:15:49.162
He's in the infirmary.

199
00:15:58.508 --> 00:16:01.595
We've neutralised the hive ships.
activated the shields

200
00:16:02.012 --> 00:16:06.851
and we've mustered as many people as we can.
making sure there are no Wraith hiding in the shadows.

201
00:16:06.851 --> 00:16:09.480
- Good work Major.
- Thank you. Sir.

202
00:16:10.523 --> 00:16:13.610
They're shipping me out
with the next batch of wounded.

203
00:16:15.153 --> 00:16:17.782
I wanted to finish our conversation.

204
00:16:19.784 --> 00:16:21.370
Yes Sir.

205
00:16:21.704 --> 00:16:25.500
I owe you an apology.

206
00:16:28.880 --> 00:16:30.798
No Sir. you don't.

207
00:16:31.132 --> 00:16:34.177
I think I have a pretty good idea.

208
00:16:36.138 --> 00:16:41.020
I would have done the same thing as you did.
when you found Colonel Sumner.

209
00:16:43.480 --> 00:16:45.692
That's what I wanted to tell you.

210
00:16:47.277 --> 00:16:49.697
None of that matters right now. Sir.

211
00:16:50.990 --> 00:16:52.868
I'm trying to say.

212
00:16:54.453 --> 00:16:57.248
I wish you had been there for me.

213
00:17:05.675 --> 00:17:09.855
- You're gonna be fine Sir. once you get back to Earth.
- I said what I had to say.

214
00:17:12.434 --> 00:17:14.228
Get back to work.

215
00:17:22.112 --> 00:17:23.949
Yes Sir.

216
00:17:31.542 --> 00:17:33.627
Preliminary count is 40 casualties.

217
00:17:34.211 --> 00:17:38.132
Maybe more. I'm still trying to line up
life signs readings with actual people.

218
00:17:38.132 --> 00:17:39.885
There are no Wraith life signs?

219
00:17:39.885 --> 00:17:43.210
The last one was trapped in one
of the deeper parts of the city.

220
00:17:43.765 --> 00:17:47.019
He died trying to damage city
with one of their grenades.

221
00:17:47.061 --> 00:17:50.791
Three of our men were injured.
On the bright side. there was no flooding.

222
00:17:50.983 --> 00:17:53.048
Have we been able to locate Lt Ford?

223
00:17:54.779 --> 00:17:55.854
I'm sorry. no.

224
00:17:55.947 --> 00:18:00.911
We searched everywhere in the city. It's possible
he may have beamed up into one of the Wraith Darts.

225
00:18:00.911 --> 00:18:02.706
Let's not make that assumption.

226
00:18:02.706 --> 00:18:04.958
Major. I'm sorry.
We searched everywhere inside the city.

227
00:18:04.958 --> 00:18:06.843
Well how about outside the city?

228
00:18:06.961 --> 00:18:10.382
- I don't understand.
- Expand the sensors. Maybe he's in the water.

229
00:18:10.382 --> 00:18:11.967
Even if that was the case. there's no chance...

230
00:18:11.967 --> 00:18:16.327
Look. I'm not asking you to swim out there.
I'm asking you to press a few damn buttons!

231
00:18:16.639 --> 00:18:18.884
Even if you're right. I don't see how...

232
00:18:22.022 --> 00:18:23.982
Oh my God.

233
00:18:33.870 --> 00:18:38.459
Colonel Caldwell? One of our men is
in the ocean outside our shield. Most probably injured.

234
00:18:38.959 --> 00:18:41.924
Can you beam him to your ship
and down to our infirmary?

235
00:18:47.803 --> 00:18:50.682
Atlantis? This is Dr Novak on the Daedalus.

236
00:18:50.682 --> 00:18:53.853
<i>You're gonna need some SO's in your infirmary.</i>
<i>before we beam your man down.</i>

237
00:18:53.853 --> 00:18:55.738
We already do Doctor. Beam away.

238
00:19:01.279 --> 00:19:02.405
Good Lord!

239
00:19:04.533 --> 00:19:06.418
Let's get this thing off of him.

240
00:19:13.086 --> 00:19:14.128
<i>How is he?</i>

241
00:19:14.671 --> 00:19:18.467
<i>I gave him a mild sedative to help rest.</i>
<i>but he should be dead.</i>

242
00:19:19.219 --> 00:19:20.679
<i>He's a tough kid.</i>

243
00:19:20.679 --> 00:19:24.892
Not my point. Major. He was lying face
down in the freezing water for over an hour.

244
00:19:25.101 --> 00:19:26.937
I don't care how tough he is.

245
00:19:27.020 --> 00:19:28.397
So what are you saying?

246
00:19:28.397 --> 00:19:29.856
We still have no idea how it works.

247
00:19:29.856 --> 00:19:33.778
but during the Wraith feeding process.
the victim is injected with a special enzyme.

248
00:19:33.778 --> 00:19:38.138
It strengthens the human body temporarily
and ensures that the heart continues to beat.

249
00:19:38.284 --> 00:19:40.453
Why would they wanna make you stronger?

250
00:19:40.453 --> 00:19:42.608
So the victim doesn't die immediately.

251
00:19:42.832 --> 00:19:45.585
The feeding process is so traumatic.
that without the special enzyme.

252
00:19:45.585 --> 00:19:47.785
we shut down far sooner than they like.

253
00:19:48.088 --> 00:19:51.323
They make you stronger
so they can take more time to kill you.

254
00:19:51.342 --> 00:19:52.635
Lovely. isn't it?

255
00:19:53.261 --> 00:19:58.071
In most cases the enzyme is released slowly
into the blood stream throughout the feeding process.

256
00:19:58.476 --> 00:20:01.441
I can only ascertain that
the Wraith died quite suddenly

257
00:20:01.939 --> 00:20:04.483
and that Lt Ford's system became flooded with it.

258
00:20:04.483 --> 00:20:07.195
And that's why he was able
to survive in the water for so long.

259
00:20:07.195 --> 00:20:08.000
Exactly.

260
00:20:08.363 --> 00:20:12.702
The problem is. now the enzyme is breaking
down in his system. eventually there'll be none left.

261
00:20:12.702 --> 00:20:14.079
That's not good.

262
00:20:14.288 --> 00:20:17.124
No. In fact. I'm quite certain it'll kill him.

263
00:20:17.834 --> 00:20:20.962
<i>It's possible his body's become</i>
<i>dependant on the enzyme to function.</i>

264
00:20:20.962 --> 00:20:22.256
What's the treatment?

265
00:20:22.256 --> 00:20:26.031
We wean him off it. Sneak his body
chemistry back to normal incrementally.

266
00:20:26.303 --> 00:20:28.597
Then we're gonna have to get more of this enzyme.

267
00:20:28.597 --> 00:20:30.725
Aye. With your permission Doctor.

268
00:20:30.934 --> 00:20:34.355
I'd like to harvest it from the Wraith bodies
in the morgue. I know it's a little bit creepy. but...

269
00:20:34.355 --> 00:20:35.970
<i>Elizabeth. Major Sheppard?</i>

270
00:20:36.858 --> 00:20:38.518
Do whatever you have to do.

271
00:20:38.777 --> 00:20:41.337
- What is it?
- You're gonna wanna get up here.

272
00:20:55.255 --> 00:20:57.592
Aren't you supposed to be getting some sleep. Rodney?

273
00:20:57.592 --> 00:21:01.180
I was trying to do just that. but someone thought I should
know the deep space sensors were back up and running.

274
00:21:01.180 --> 00:21:02.056
Yes. and?

275
00:21:03.349 --> 00:21:06.449
They picked up 12 more hive ships
travelling in hyperspace.

276
00:21:06.770 --> 00:21:10.775
Their course and speed will
bring them here in 36 hours.

277
00:21:27.797 --> 00:21:29.632
12 hive ships?

278
00:21:30.341 --> 00:21:33.576
The Cruisers that got away
probably called for reinforcements.

279
00:21:33.595 --> 00:21:37.392
Our research shows there are
at least 60 hive ships in this galaxy.

280
00:21:37.684 --> 00:21:39.770
But who knows how many more could be on the way?

281
00:21:39.770 --> 00:21:42.481
- At least the shield's up and running.
- That only buys us time!

282
00:21:42.481 --> 00:21:43.442
I like time.

283
00:21:43.442 --> 00:21:46.696
Look. the first siege of Atlantis lasted for years.
I mean.

284
00:21:46.904 --> 00:21:50.241
with only one functioning ZPM.
we can't expect to hold on that long.

285
00:21:50.241 --> 00:21:52.081
Can we submerge the city again?

286
00:21:52.786 --> 00:21:54.956
It's a city. not a yo-yo.

287
00:21:55.206 --> 00:21:57.417
Look. I don't even know
how they did it the first time.

288
00:21:57.417 --> 00:21:59.077
How long until they arrive?

289
00:21:59.545 --> 00:22:00.890
A little over a day.

290
00:22:01.881 --> 00:22:03.133
You know what?

291
00:22:04.426 --> 00:22:05.636
I'm sick of this.

292
00:22:06.429 --> 00:22:07.324
I'm sorry?

293
00:22:07.639 --> 00:22:11.864
I mean. sitting around waiting for them to show up.
I say we take the fight to them.

294
00:22:12.061 --> 00:22:13.103
We've got one ship. Major.

295
00:22:13.103 --> 00:22:17.463
We got one ship with an Asgard shield.
an armoury full of nukes and beaming technology.

296
00:22:17.526 --> 00:22:20.655
- That evens the odds out a lot.
- Twelve ships and their escorts.

297
00:22:20.655 --> 00:22:23.575
I'm telling you.
We've gotta send these guys a message.

298
00:22:23.867 --> 00:22:26.663
We're not like the Ancients.
We're not gonna sit around and wait.

299
00:22:26.663 --> 00:22:27.622
If they don't back off.

300
00:22:27.622 --> 00:22:31.217
we have the capacity and the will
to go kick their asses for a change.

301
00:22:31.835 --> 00:22:33.900
How do I fight a ship in hyperspace?

302
00:22:34.255 --> 00:22:38.750
The Wraith's faster than light travel is not
as the Asgard hyperdrive aboard the Daedalus.

303
00:22:39.762 --> 00:22:43.225
Not only slower.
they need to travel in a series of jumps.

304
00:22:43.558 --> 00:22:45.561
So if my calculations are correct.

305
00:22:46.604 --> 00:22:51.594
they'll make one last stop here. fifty light years away.
before they make the final jump to Atlantis.

306
00:22:52.362 --> 00:22:53.488
Dr Weir?

307
00:22:55.198 --> 00:22:58.388
It will feel good to have them
on the defensive for a change.

308
00:22:59.286 --> 00:23:00.539
Alright then.

309
00:23:02.457 --> 00:23:04.168
let's do this.

310
00:23:15.933 --> 00:23:18.352
Scanners are clear. Sir. No contacts.

311
00:23:18.394 --> 00:23:19.980
I hope we're in the right spot.

312
00:23:19.980 --> 00:23:23.305
They'll be here.
I'm willing to trust Rodney about these things.

313
00:23:25.862 --> 00:23:29.825
I've set the warheads to go off
one second after reintegration.

314
00:23:31.328 --> 00:23:34.372
So I assume you're fine with that?

315
00:23:40.088 --> 00:23:41.256
OK...

316
00:23:44.635 --> 00:23:47.014
They are angry. I can feel it.

317
00:23:47.473 --> 00:23:51.158
Word of our success might spread to other worlds.
They want us silenced.

318
00:23:51.645 --> 00:23:53.146
You can sense that?

319
00:23:53.730 --> 00:23:56.484
The Wraith warrior were in such close proximity...

320
00:23:57.818 --> 00:23:59.488
Excuse me.

321
00:23:59.863 --> 00:24:00.572
Ford!

322
00:24:00.822 --> 00:24:02.797
I'd like to report for duty ma'am.

323
00:24:03.868 --> 00:24:05.787
Dr. Beckett released you?

324
00:24:06.747 --> 00:24:08.499
Why wouldn't he. I'm fine.

325
00:24:12.796 --> 00:24:17.218
If we can hit the first one or two as soon as
they exit hyperspace. I think that'll send a message.

326
00:24:17.218 --> 00:24:18.720
Who knows. maybe they'll surrender.

327
00:24:18.720 --> 00:24:19.971
Sir. we have a contact.

328
00:24:19.971 --> 00:24:22.558
Stand by for weapons deployment.
Shields at max power.

329
00:24:22.558 --> 00:24:23.498
Shields up.

330
00:24:29.275 --> 00:24:32.237
Novak. this is Caldwell.
Begin deployment at your discretion.

331
00:24:32.237 --> 00:24:35.950
I have a weapons lock on the
coordinates of the first enemy vessel.

332
00:24:36.409 --> 00:24:38.870
Got it! First weapon away. Colonel.

333
00:24:44.168 --> 00:24:45.421
That's a kill.

334
00:24:46.088 --> 00:24:47.256
<i>Stand by.</i>

335
00:24:53.264 --> 00:24:54.682
Alright. that's two.

336
00:24:55.641 --> 00:24:56.727
It's working.

337
00:24:57.060 --> 00:24:59.062
Stand by for coordinates.

338
00:24:59.396 --> 00:25:01.524
The other hive ships are altering course to intercept.

339
00:25:01.524 --> 00:25:03.544
- Take us right at them.
- Yes Sir.

340
00:25:09.159 --> 00:25:10.504
They're flanking us.

341
00:25:11.244 --> 00:25:12.538
Forward rail guns. return fire.

342
00:25:12.538 --> 00:25:17.078
Novak we need to speed up deployment of
those nukes or this fight is going to be over soon.

343
00:25:19.087 --> 00:25:23.761
The enemy has engaged counter measures
that are preventing our ability to transport.

344
00:25:23.844 --> 00:25:26.764
- Is there a way to counter the counter?
- None.

345
00:25:27.390 --> 00:25:32.605
<i>Colonel. we have a problem. They've found a way to jam</i>
<i>us from beaming onto their ship. We don't know how.</i>

346
00:25:33.189 --> 00:25:35.749
Rear shield emitters are down to forty percent!

347
00:25:38.820 --> 00:25:41.199
Central rail gun two is out of action!

348
00:25:41.240 --> 00:25:43.369
Take engines to max. Foster!

349
00:25:43.744 --> 00:25:46.484
Try keeping the damaged shield from the main force.

350
00:25:58.680 --> 00:26:01.915
Sir! One of the cruisers is approaching
on a parrallel course.

351
00:26:02.141 --> 00:26:06.021
They may intend to board us!
That was their strategy when they attacked Atlantis.

352
00:26:06.021 --> 00:26:07.096
Shield status?

353
00:26:07.399 --> 00:26:08.400
Under 20%.

354
00:26:08.608 --> 00:26:10.695
Set course for Atlantis. Engage hyperdrive.

355
00:26:10.695 --> 00:26:12.040
Hyperdrive. Yes Sir!

356
00:26:12.238 --> 00:26:13.538
This fight is over.

357
00:26:31.804 --> 00:26:33.644
<i>Bottom line is. it didn't work.</i>

358
00:26:33.932 --> 00:26:36.268
At least you gave them something to think about.

359
00:26:36.268 --> 00:26:41.258
We'll see. I doubt very much that that tactic won't
work again and the Daedalus has sustained damage.

360
00:26:41.316 --> 00:26:43.336
It was still the right thing to do.

361
00:26:44.570 --> 00:26:46.725
We should make it home before they do.

362
00:26:46.906 --> 00:26:49.556
<i>I hope so.</i>
<i>We'll keep the porch light on for you.</i>

363
00:26:50.953 --> 00:26:52.455
OK. what are our options?

364
00:26:52.455 --> 00:26:56.376
Well let me see. we've got slow death.
quick death. painful death. cold lonely death...

365
00:26:56.376 --> 00:27:01.133
OK. you said yourself that the shield
should buy us some time.

366
00:27:01.300 --> 00:27:02.634
Where do you want me?

367
00:27:02.634 --> 00:27:03.799
Lieutenant. I...

368
00:27:04.804 --> 00:27:07.049
Lt! What do you think you're doing here?

369
00:27:07.140 --> 00:27:09.810
- I'm fine Doc. really. It's cool.
- The hell you are. You should be back in bed.

370
00:27:09.810 --> 00:27:11.729
I feel great. Just drop it.

371
00:27:11.938 --> 00:27:15.108
I will not just drop it.
Not twenty minutes ago. you were at death's door.

372
00:27:15.108 --> 00:27:18.838
I don't care how spry you feel.
you need to be under medical supervision.

373
00:27:19.405 --> 00:27:20.949
I'm good to go.

374
00:27:21.700 --> 00:27:24.287
I appreciate your enthusiasm Lieutenant. but Doctor...

375
00:27:24.287 --> 00:27:27.792
I'm serious! Just let me prove it.
Just give me something to do.

376
00:27:27.958 --> 00:27:30.338
- I don't think so.
- Don't push me around!

377
00:27:32.464 --> 00:27:33.799
<i>Lieutenant!</i>

378
00:27:35.802 --> 00:27:38.763
Put him down Aiden. he's trying to help you.

379
00:27:42.851 --> 00:27:43.937
Aiden.

380
00:27:59.039 --> 00:28:00.374
I'm sorry Doc.

381
00:28:01.250 --> 00:28:04.710
- I don't know why I...
- You need to be under medical supervision.

382
00:28:05.213 --> 00:28:06.966
He's right. Lieutenant.

383
00:28:07.341 --> 00:28:10.306
We just wanna know why
you're suddenly feeling this way.

384
00:28:13.181 --> 00:28:13.807
OK.

385
00:28:14.517 --> 00:28:15.547
I'll go back.

386
00:28:15.977 --> 00:28:17.862
Good. that's what you should do.

387
00:28:20.774 --> 00:28:21.669
Yes ma'am.

388
00:28:30.996 --> 00:28:32.611
Sedate him if you have to.

389
00:28:32.664 --> 00:28:33.290
Aye.

390
00:28:52.899 --> 00:28:55.324
<i>It's starting to affect his brain chemistry.</i>

391
00:28:57.488 --> 00:28:59.073
<i>There's no way you could have known that Carson.</i>

392
00:28:59.073 --> 00:29:00.825
<i>and it's better this than death.</i>

393
00:29:00.825 --> 00:29:02.494
<i>We need to be more aggressive</i>

394
00:29:02.494 --> 00:29:04.739
<i>wean him off quicker than I expected to.</i>

395
00:29:04.789 --> 00:29:06.457
<i>It'll be painful and arduous.</i>

396
00:29:06.457 --> 00:29:08.612
<i>but I think it may be our only option.</i>

397
00:29:08.752 --> 00:29:10.003
Now I've sedated him.

398
00:29:10.003 --> 00:29:12.298
but he should definitely be under secure supervision.

399
00:29:12.298 --> 00:29:14.678
I've already stationed a guard at the door.

400
00:29:15.009 --> 00:29:15.843
<i>Doctor Weir.</i>

401
00:29:15.843 --> 00:29:19.123
<i>the Daedalus is requesting</i>
<i>permission to land on the east pier.</i>

402
00:29:20.016 --> 00:29:22.306
Permission granted. I'll meet them there.

403
00:29:41.501 --> 00:29:43.212
Welcome back to Atlantis. Colonel.

404
00:29:43.212 --> 00:29:44.630
The Wraith are right behind us.

405
00:29:44.630 --> 00:29:45.673
I wasn't expecting you to land.

406
00:29:45.673 --> 00:29:49.845
Until repairs are complete. the Daedalus is going
to need Atlantis' shields as much as you do.

407
00:29:49.845 --> 00:29:50.595
<i>Doctor Weir.</i>

408
00:29:50.595 --> 00:29:52.974
<i>the hive ships are emmerging from hyperspace.</i>

409
00:29:52.974 --> 00:29:54.184
We're on our way.

410
00:30:06.742 --> 00:30:08.827
- Ford!
- Don't move or I'll shoot!

411
00:30:11.330 --> 00:30:12.999
Where's the rest of the enzyme!

412
00:30:12.999 --> 00:30:13.624
There is no more.

413
00:30:13.624 --> 00:30:15.711
I saw you extract it. don't lie to me!
Where is it?

414
00:30:15.711 --> 00:30:16.966
No. I'm not lying!

415
00:30:20.216 --> 00:30:21.201
Where is it?

416
00:30:21.342 --> 00:30:23.272
You're not thinking straight son.

417
00:30:24.263 --> 00:30:25.431
You're all afraid of me.

418
00:30:25.431 --> 00:30:27.809
Look at what you're doing.
we have good reason to be.

419
00:30:27.809 --> 00:30:29.812
- I'm gonna die if I don't get it!
- Aiden. you're not gonna die.

420
00:30:29.812 --> 00:30:30.617
Shut up!

421
00:30:36.987 --> 00:30:38.512
I'm not gonna ask again.

422
00:30:59.099 --> 00:31:00.354
Is that all of it?

423
00:31:01.811 --> 00:31:03.896
- I promise you.
- Toss it over.

424
00:31:04.940 --> 00:31:05.745
Toss it!

425
00:31:12.741 --> 00:31:13.906
Don't follow me.

426
00:31:23.379 --> 00:31:25.804
They're getting into some sort of formation.

427
00:31:27.259 --> 00:31:28.199
Move. move!

428
00:31:48.327 --> 00:31:50.830
The shield's holding under bombardment.
but it's under incredible strain.

429
00:31:50.830 --> 00:31:52.082
How long will it hold?

430
00:31:52.082 --> 00:31:54.501
Well if they stop firing at it.
it'll last almost indefinitely.

431
00:31:54.501 --> 00:31:56.171
- but with this kind of...
- Are we talking months. weeks?

432
00:31:56.171 --> 00:31:56.841
Days.

433
00:31:57.922 --> 00:32:00.617
At this rate the ZPM will be depleted within days.

434
00:32:09.900 --> 00:32:11.300
It's almost pretty. isn't it?

435
00:32:11.300 --> 00:32:13.569
Almost. But not quite.

436
00:32:20.064 --> 00:32:22.733
We need to get the Daedalus back
into fighting form within 24 hours.

437
00:32:22.733 --> 00:32:25.833
but I think the next engagement
gonna have the same result.

438
00:32:26.237 --> 00:32:29.247
Even if we were able to destroy
these ships this instant.

439
00:32:29.323 --> 00:32:32.577
more would be here in a few days
and even more a few days after that.

440
00:32:32.577 --> 00:32:35.288
From where I'm standing
I just don't see how we can win this.

441
00:32:35.288 --> 00:32:37.938
Well now we know how the Ancients must have felt.

442
00:32:38.000 --> 00:32:39.877
Atlantis is the only way to Earth.

443
00:32:39.877 --> 00:32:41.762
As long as they know we're here.

444
00:32:41.837 --> 00:32:43.812
they're just going to keep coming.

445
00:32:43.839 --> 00:32:45.949
As long as they know that we're here.

446
00:32:46.466 --> 00:32:47.676
What do you mean?

447
00:32:48.010 --> 00:32:51.138
Zelenka just said that as long as they know
that we're here. they'll keep coming.

448
00:32:51.138 --> 00:32:52.393
Yes. he said that.

449
00:32:53.016 --> 00:32:54.517
Well what if they thought we were gone?

450
00:32:54.517 --> 00:32:56.978
Then there'd be no reason for them to stay.

451
00:32:57.103 --> 00:32:57.908
Exactly.

452
00:32:58.354 --> 00:32:59.384
Exactly what?

453
00:32:59.898 --> 00:33:00.928
We disappear.

454
00:33:03.943 --> 00:33:05.111
Destroy the city you mean?

455
00:33:05.111 --> 00:33:07.221
No. we just make it look like we did.

456
00:33:07.947 --> 00:33:08.572
How?

457
00:33:09.491 --> 00:33:10.326
We cloak it.

458
00:33:10.326 --> 00:33:12.119
Yes. yes!

459
00:33:12.119 --> 00:33:14.914
The Puddle Jumpers are equipped
with cloaking technology.

460
00:33:14.914 --> 00:33:18.334
which renders them invisible to the naked eye
and to Wraith scans.

461
00:33:18.334 --> 00:33:21.795
If we just simply remove one of the cloak generators
from the Puddle Jumper...

462
00:33:21.795 --> 00:33:23.130
I wouldn't say simply. but yes.

463
00:33:23.130 --> 00:33:25.341
by interfacing a Jumper's

464
00:33:25.382 --> 00:33:29.095
stealth mode generator with the city's shield.
we should be able to render the city invisible.

465
00:33:29.095 --> 00:33:29.971
That's all well and good.

466
00:33:29.971 --> 00:33:33.099
but I think if the city were to suddenly disappear.
they might be able to put one and one together.

467
00:33:33.099 --> 00:33:35.143
Which is why we fake a self destruct.

468
00:33:35.143 --> 00:33:39.143
Have the Daedalus beam a nuke right
above the city shield and then detonate it.

469
00:33:39.564 --> 00:33:42.234
While their sensors are blinded. we cloak the city.

470
00:33:42.234 --> 00:33:43.069
When the smoke clears...

471
00:33:43.069 --> 00:33:44.320
Nothing but ocean.

472
00:33:44.320 --> 00:33:45.738
What about high radiation?

473
00:33:45.738 --> 00:33:48.741
I should be able to calculate with reasonable accuracy.
how long to wait before we switch over to the cloak.

474
00:33:48.741 --> 00:33:50.409
But what about the displacement issues?

475
00:33:50.409 --> 00:33:52.119
It's called planet emulation.That's the easy part.

476
00:33:52.119 --> 00:33:54.247
OK. What about the hard part?

477
00:33:55.373 --> 00:33:56.268
Hard part?

478
00:33:56.415 --> 00:33:59.336
Ah! The cloak. for all intents and purposes.
will replace the shield.

479
00:33:59.336 --> 00:34:03.201
which means that we'll be
completely unprotected once the cloak's activated.

480
00:34:03.507 --> 00:34:04.967
We'll be completely exposed?

481
00:34:04.967 --> 00:34:07.052
Well... yes.

482
00:34:07.803 --> 00:34:09.304
So if they're not fooled by the ruse...

483
00:34:09.304 --> 00:34:13.799
Then they destroy the city. which I remind
you is exactly what we were going to do anyway.

484
00:34:15.185 --> 00:34:16.020
What about the Daedalus?

485
00:34:16.020 --> 00:34:17.105
Well if it doesn't work.

486
00:34:17.105 --> 00:34:20.066
our shields should be sufficiently recharged
to break through their lines and escape.

487
00:34:20.066 --> 00:34:21.276
We know we can outrun them.

488
00:34:21.276 --> 00:34:26.865
Alright. Let's get as many non essential personnel
onto your ship as we can. Just in case.

489
00:34:27.490 --> 00:34:29.367
I love this idea. I really do.

490
00:34:29.576 --> 00:34:33.539
But the Wraith are aware
that we have cloaking technology.

491
00:34:34.373 --> 00:34:35.493
They are close.

492
00:34:36.667 --> 00:34:38.867
Close enough for me to connect to them.

493
00:34:39.587 --> 00:34:43.924
If I can convince them that we intend
to destroy Atlantis rather than allow it to be taken.

494
00:34:43.924 --> 00:34:46.051
just before the explosion occurs.

495
00:34:46.260 --> 00:34:48.429
How will we know whether or not they believe you?

496
00:34:48.429 --> 00:34:50.809
Once they stop the bombardment. we'll know.

497
00:34:51.057 --> 00:34:51.997
He's right.

498
00:34:52.726 --> 00:34:55.896
If the Wraith believe that
we intend to destroy the city.

499
00:34:56.688 --> 00:34:59.518
the last thing they'll wanna do.
is to help us do it.

500
00:35:01.276 --> 00:35:02.611
How much time do you need?

501
00:35:02.611 --> 00:35:03.361
Oh uh...

502
00:35:03.361 --> 00:35:04.613
- Week.
- Couple of hours.

503
00:35:04.613 --> 00:35:06.588
I'll take the second estimate.
Go!

504
00:35:09.202 --> 00:35:10.119
You're in union?

505
00:35:10.119 --> 00:35:11.284
Couple of hours.

506
00:35:17.543 --> 00:35:18.483
He escaped.

507
00:35:18.586 --> 00:35:19.661
- What?
- Who?

508
00:35:20.379 --> 00:35:24.468
Ford. He was able to disarm one of the marines
and got away with all the Wraith enzyme I had left.

509
00:35:24.468 --> 00:35:26.353
Ford. this is Sheppard. come in.

510
00:35:27.346 --> 00:35:31.308
Ford? I need you to come back
to the control room buddy. we're all going home.

511
00:35:34.019 --> 00:35:35.479
<i>Lt do you copy?</i>

512
00:35:37.272 --> 00:35:39.112
You're just afraid of me Major.

513
00:35:39.442 --> 00:35:41.462
You're afraid of what I can do now.

514
00:35:42.654 --> 00:35:44.224
I'm not listening to you.

515
00:35:46.324 --> 00:35:47.669
I'm going after him.

516
00:35:48.826 --> 00:35:50.396
Now's not the right time!

517
00:36:30.246 --> 00:36:33.457
Now I'm jolting you out of this the second
I feel there's a problem.

518
00:36:33.457 --> 00:36:34.487
I understand.

519
00:36:36.586 --> 00:36:37.837
We're all set down here.

520
00:36:37.837 --> 00:36:39.922
Good! We're almost ready up here. Rodney?

521
00:36:39.922 --> 00:36:40.548
Ready!

522
00:36:40.548 --> 00:36:41.263
Radek!

523
00:36:43.885 --> 00:36:44.870
Ready to go.

524
00:36:46.805 --> 00:36:48.015
<i>Colonel Caldwell.</i>

525
00:36:48.056 --> 00:36:49.349
The people are securely aboard.

526
00:36:49.349 --> 00:36:52.144
The warhead has been armed
and is ready for deployment on your mark.

527
00:36:52.144 --> 00:36:53.489
<i>Very good! Stand by!</i>

528
00:37:13.708 --> 00:37:14.648
Dr Beckett?

529
00:37:17.045 --> 00:37:17.760
Teyla.

530
00:37:18.714 --> 00:37:19.757
I'm ready.

531
00:37:21.634 --> 00:37:22.844
We're good to go.

532
00:37:23.719 --> 00:37:25.604
Alright. let's send our message.

533
00:37:43.323 --> 00:37:44.893
I am on one of the ships.

534
00:37:47.911 --> 00:37:48.896
They see me.

535
00:37:56.837 --> 00:37:57.552
Teyla?

536
00:37:59.382 --> 00:38:01.222
The message has been delivered.

537
00:38:01.259 --> 00:38:02.649
Elizabeth. it's done.

538
00:38:13.272 --> 00:38:15.440
Seems that they heard Teyla loud and clear.
Rodney?

539
00:38:15.440 --> 00:38:17.640
- Yeah! I think I'm ready.
- You think?

540
00:38:18.151 --> 00:38:19.586
I am definitely ready.

541
00:38:21.280 --> 00:38:22.739
Daedalus. launch the weapon.

542
00:38:22.739 --> 00:38:23.994
Give me city wide.

543
00:38:24.616 --> 00:38:27.491
Attention all personnel.
Prepare for detonation flash.

544
00:38:27.954 --> 00:38:29.205
Shut 'em down!

545
00:38:38.172 --> 00:38:39.472
The weapon is away.

546
00:38:57.985 --> 00:38:58.945
Rodney?

547
00:38:59.154 --> 00:39:03.825
If we switch to cloak before the blast radius diminishes.
we'll all be incinerated. Five seconds.

548
00:39:03.825 --> 00:39:06.328
Stand by to engage sublight engines on my mark.

549
00:39:06.328 --> 00:39:07.493
Standing by Sir.

550
00:39:14.461 --> 00:39:16.751
I think that was definitely five seconds.

551
00:39:17.173 --> 00:39:18.248
We're cloaked.

552
00:39:19.050 --> 00:39:20.260
How can you tell?

553
00:39:20.927 --> 00:39:22.452
They're scanning for us.

554
00:39:28.226 --> 00:39:30.786
I could have shot you a couple of times by now.

555
00:39:33.357 --> 00:39:36.151
Well. I'm glad you didn't.

556
00:39:39.279 --> 00:39:39.949
Look.

557
00:39:41.240 --> 00:39:45.118
why don't you and I just go someplace
where we can talk.

558
00:39:45.536 --> 00:39:46.995
You're trying to change me back.

559
00:39:46.995 --> 00:39:49.707
No. I'm just trying to help you.

560
00:39:57.215 --> 00:39:58.466
No you're not.

561
00:39:59.217 --> 00:39:59.926
Crap.

562
00:40:11.397 --> 00:40:13.372
I don't think they've detected us.

563
00:40:14.942 --> 00:40:16.422
Why are you whispering?

564
00:40:17.653 --> 00:40:20.573
I don't know. it just
seems like the right thing to do.

565
00:40:21.408 --> 00:40:22.798
Is it working or not?

566
00:40:34.254 --> 00:40:35.589
What the hell...?

567
00:40:43.306 --> 00:40:43.931
That's Ford.

568
00:40:43.931 --> 00:40:46.017
I assume that's him in the Jumper?

569
00:40:49.896 --> 00:40:51.564
- Can they detect that?
- I don't know.

570
00:40:51.564 --> 00:40:52.273
Shut it down!

571
00:40:52.273 --> 00:40:54.158
I can't the Jumper's in control!

572
00:40:56.236 --> 00:40:59.990
Ford! Stand down. this is a direct order!

573
00:41:16.549 --> 00:41:18.209
Where the hell is he going?

574
00:41:19.802 --> 00:41:23.556
It won't matter if the Wraith can detect
the gate activity through the cloak.

575
00:41:23.556 --> 00:41:25.306
There's only one way to know.

576
00:41:31.899 --> 00:41:35.674
<i>This is Daedalus. Our sensors indicate</i>
<i>the Wraith fleet is breaking orbit.</i>

577
00:41:38.030 --> 00:41:39.330
I can confirm that.

578
00:41:39.531 --> 00:41:40.991
They're headed for hyperspace.

579
00:41:40.991 --> 00:41:44.406
Look. I'm gonna keep the cloak up
for a while just to be sure. but

580
00:41:44.621 --> 00:41:46.101
I think they bought it.

581
00:41:57.759 --> 00:42:00.262
The gate address will be in the log.
There's still a chance...

582
00:42:00.262 --> 00:42:02.012
Doesn't matter where he goes.

583
00:42:02.765 --> 00:42:05.059
The second he gets to wherever he's going.

584
00:42:05.059 --> 00:42:06.764
he's gonna ditch the Jumper.

585
00:42:07.061 --> 00:42:08.046
turn around.

586
00:42:08.813 --> 00:42:11.283
and dial another address. One we can't trace.

587
00:42:12.233 --> 00:42:13.353
We'll find him.

588
00:42:13.818 --> 00:42:14.533
Maybe.

589
00:42:19.866 --> 00:42:21.886
At least we're still around to try.

590
00:42:25.497 --> 00:42:26.167
Yeah.
